Finds custom comparison values

Source: R/compareHelpers.R
get_comparison_values.Rd

Finds custom comparison values

Usage

get_comparison_values(d, comp_histories)

Arguments

d

data frame of high and low values per exposure main effect

comp_histories

comparison sequence(s) of "h" and/or "l" (e.g., "h-h-h")

Value

comparison values

Examples

d <- data.frame(
  e = c("A.1", "A.2", "A.3"),
  l = c(0, 0, 0),
  h = c(1, 1, 1)
)
r <- get_comparison_values(
  d = d,
  comp_histories = "l-l-l"
)
#> Error in get_comparison_values(d = d, comp_histories = "l-l-l"): could not find function "get_comparison_values"
r <- get_comparison_values(
  d = d,
  comp_histories = "h-h-h"
)
#> Error in get_comparison_values(d = d, comp_histories = "h-h-h"): could not find function "get_comparison_values"
r <- get_comparison_values(
  d = d,
  comp_histories = c("h-h-h", "h-h-l")
)
#> Error in get_comparison_values(d = d, comp_histories = c("h-h-h", "h-h-l")): could not find function "get_comparison_values"
